    "text": "JOHANNESBURG (Reuters) - South Africa on Tuesday declared drought a national disaster after reassessing the “magnitude and severity” in three drought-stricken provinces, including the area around Cape Town.\nSouth Africa is battling a drought that is part of a wider climate change pattern seen around the country. The Western Cape, Northern Cape and Eastern Cape provinces have been worst hit.\nReporting by Nqobile Dludla; Editing by James Macharia\n ",
